Avro file formats

1) It is a row based file format
2) Good for writing the data (faster reads) but nt ideal for reading (slower reads)
3) Stores the metadata in JSON file format
4) Original data is stored in binary format
5) Good support for schema evolution (renaming columns and adding new columns)
6) Words well with all the languages (Java,C,C++,Python) quite the generic one.
